# pytest-optimizer commit template -- ONE speedup per commit.
# Adapt the type(scope) prefix to THIS project's convention (read its AGENTS.md /
# CLAUDE.md). Lines beginning with '#' are stripped by git.
#
# Subject <= 50 chars. Body wrapped at <= 72. Keep one blank line between why and
# what. State the MEASURED problem and the MEASURED result -- not a narration of
# the diff.

<type>(<scope>) <imperative summary of the single change>

why: <the measured problem this fixes -- what was slow and by how much, e.g.
     "make_config ran 40x at function scope (~0.3s each, ~12s of setup)">

what:
- <the single change applied>
- <measured delta: suite X.Xs -> Y.Ys (-Z%), above the k*MAD noise band>

Refs: pytest-optimizer <heuristic-id>
